{As our speakers shared at our 'Back to Business' briefing yesterday- business travel is back as brands see the value in face-to-face connections once again with new airport passenger insight unveiled ➡ #OOH #OOH #airportadvertising h #digitalmarketing https://t.co/UOzQAorm22} as string,

{If you'd like to know more about this new Airport insight do drop us a line - and to read the press release with topline results click here. https://t.co/QunynkanIg} as string,

{Samantha Zwertvaegher, Cisco explains that being top of mind is key for the brand, and they chose to invest in airport advertising so they could benefit from the perceived value it offered and the BDMs looking for new opportunities whilst travelling for work. #BacktoBusiness https://t.co/3z1a2JfNWF} as string,
{Peter Colvin describes the airport as “the ultimate platform to showcase your global brand credentials to an engaged elite” #BacktoBusiness https://t.co/hWn8bAxHR4} as string,
{“Rate of converting prospects to actual customers nearly doubles when face-to-face meetings are added” #BacktoBusiness https://t.co/M5Jc4trqez} as string,

{Peter Colvin, Global Media and Communications Consultant explains the importance of face-to-face interactions with 93% of communication coming from body language and tonal cues. #BacktoBusiness https://t.co/umHzabLDRa} as string,
{The airport is a place for B2B influence with 2 in 3 respondents likely to search online for products seen advertised at the airport. #BacktoBusiness https://t.co/hQzKg4mcU7} as string,

{93% agree business travel is vital or important with the key reasons why they travel for business being building relationships, meeting clients and human interaction. #BacktoBusiness https://t.co/OAwl8zsjVk} as string,

{Laura Tanner, Head of Marketing reveals findings from our latest research - 76% of business travellers look for new opportunities while on a business trip and 60% perceive B2B brands at the airport to be market leaders. #BacktoBusiness https://t.co/EayzW6FNaM} as string,

{29% of companies surveyed by Morgan Stanley say their firms are already back to pre-covid business travel levels. 48% expect full recovery by 2025. 2023 will be the year of business travel. #BacktoBusiness https://t.co/C6lXlkoLRG} as string,

{David Hawkins, Commercial and Partnerships Director – Airport, kicks off with the latest airport traffic forecasts, which are expected to return to 93% of pre-pandemic figures in 2023. #BacktoBusiness https://t.co/B89a5ann6C} as string,
